The Tailwind CDN warning is separate and can be addressed in production deployment by using Tailwind CLI or PostCSS plugin configuration.

## Impact
- ✅ All settings components now export consistently
- ✅ Barrel export (index.ts) works correctly
- ✅ Backward compatibility maintained with default exports
- ✅ No breaking changes to existing imports
- ✅ Full named export support for tree-shaking optimization

## Backward Compatibility
All existing default imports continue to work:
```tsx
// Still works (default import)
import SettingsCard from './SettingsCard';

// Now also works (named import)
import { SettingsCard } from './SettingsCard';

// And works with barrel export (named import)
import { SettingsCard } from './index';
```
